Algorithm:
Step 1: First calculate  k % nums.length , this tells how many times we are rotating the array heling avoide multiple iterations.
Step 2: Now we call a child function called reverse which will reverse the array. First we rotate the whole array, then we rotate left to k - 1 and then k to nums.length-1



Code:
class Solution {
    public void rotate(int[] nums, int k) {
        
        k = k % nums.length;

        reverse(nums,0, nums.length - 1);
        reverse(nums, 0, k-1);
        reverse(nums, k , nums.length-1);
    }

    public void reverse(int[] nums, int left, int right)
    {
        while(left < right)
        {
            int temp = nums[left];
            nums[left] = nums[right];
            nums[right] = temp;

            left++;
            right--;
        }
    }
}
